	   <tr><td colspan=2>Clarity as a right-click? Rock.<br><br>As a 55 Enchanter, I am constantly in raid-type situations where you have a total wipe-out from people not assisting, or mobs coming too fast, or whatever... there are so many variables in a big raid you can't really place blame. Anyway, when the cleric has just rezzed you, and everyone is trying to get to combat readiness as fast as possible, a free Clarity is invaluable to toss on clerics, newly rezzed party members, and your newly rezzed self in an attempt to get everybody moving again. Absolutely PERFECT for Plane of Sky raids, when people have to axe themselves in order to move to the next island.<br><br>In general situations, yes, you're going to want to use C2 all the time. But when you're trying to recover from mass rezzings, this effect will cut your downtime in half, at least, until you can get back up enough mana to start C2-ing everybody around you. And downtime only makes people bored and angry.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
